Additional licenses / components
--------------------------------

Some components in Catel are based on other open-source components. Each component
that is based on another component has a reference to the original component including
the original license the code was delivered upon. Below is a list of these components:

* DynamicEventListener
  http://stackoverflow.com/questions/8122085/calling-an-instance-method-when-event-occurs/8122242#8122242
  Original license: CC BY-SA 2.5, compatible with the MIT license.

* TypeHelper.IsSubclassOfRawGeneric
  http://stackoverflow.com/questions/457676/c-reflection-check-if-a-class-is-derived-from-a-generic-class
  Original license: CC BY-SA 2.5, compatible with the MIT license.

* MethodToValueConverter
  http://stackoverflow.com/questions/502250/bind-to-a-method-in-wpf
  Original license: CC BY-SA 2.5, compatible with the MIT license.

* ObjectExtensions.IsSentinelBindingObject
  http://stackoverflow.com/questions/3868786/wpf-sentinel-objects-and-how-to-check-for-an-internal-type
  Original license: CC BY-SA 2.5, compatible with the MIT license.
  
* DragDrop
  http://wpfbehaviorlibrary.codeplex.com/, which is based on http://gallery.expression.microsoft.com/DragDropBehavior/
  Original license: Ms-Pl, compatible with the MIT license.

* ValueConverterGroup
  http://www.codeproject.com/KB/WPF/PipingValueConverters_WPF.aspx
  Original license: CPOL, compatible with the MIT license.
  
If you think that this list is incomplete, let us know.